title.narrative: Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#2 KEPI and CEPI tools)

Kenyan national Environmental Performance Index (KEPI) and County EPI (CEPI) tools in place and used to support DEF: as measured by the number KEPI and CEPI assessments made. Measured every 2 years (in 2018 and 2020)
Enhanced Private Sector adoption of green technologies and practices through PPPs (#2 economic instruments)

Number of economic instruments related to the policy level implemented
(targets solid waste management in selected Counties, royalty charges and user fees, etc.).
In line with the "Guidelines on Economic Instruments for Env. Mgmnt. in Kenya".
Reduced environmental crime (#4 Rapid Environmental Response Framework)
Rapid Environmental Response Framework (RERF) in place and operational.
Reduced environmental crime (#5 Environmental crime index)
Environmental Crime Incidents Index (ECII) in place and used to track environmental crime.
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#3 CEAPs developed)
Number of National and County Ennvironmental Action Plans (CEAPs) developed. (Based on the original DED indicator and used up to June 2019.)
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#5 ecosystem plans)
Number of ecosystems with management plans
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#4 SEA checklist)
Number of CIDPs subjected to SEA checklist.
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#6 Green Points)
Number of "Green Points" (GPs) operational and undertaking community engagement and outreach programmes on green technologies and information.
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (DEF) (#7 Devolved Environmental Functions)

Number of Counties trained and capable of effectively implementing selected Devolved Environmental Functions (DEF) i.e. waste management, noise pollution and environmental planning (inspections, enforcements, licensing and permitting).
Enhanced Private Sector adoption of green technologies and practices through PPPs (#1 environmental compliance/ cleaner production scheme)
No. of private sector companies (PSCS) (manufacturing, building and construction) participating in voluntary environmental compliance and/or cleaner production schemes (milestone targets)

Environmental functions mainstreamed in ministries, departments and agencies (MDAs) and their implementation reported back to the Performance Contracting Secretariat (#2 sustainable production and consumption)
Number of MDAs practicing sustainable production and consumption as a result of increased knowledge and awareness facilitated by NEMA. (Milestone indicator)
Reduced environmental crime (#1 licences /permits)
Total number of licenses / permits issued annually during this DE.
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (DEF) (#1 County Environment Commitees)

No of counties that have gazetted county environmental committees (CEC's)
The level of achievement has been downscaled to CECs being gazetted (rather than "established and functional") in line with the "Deep Dive" recommendation and budget cut of the MTR.
Reduced environmental crime (#2 audits)
Total number of environmental audits submitted to NEMA annually during this DE.
A greener development pathway for Kenya (Environmental Performance)

Global Environmental Performance Index (EPI) improved.
The EPI tracks how well a country performs on environmental management against two overriding issues or objectives: Environmental Health (measures the protection of human health from environmental harm) and Ecosystem Vitality (measures ecosystem protection and resource management).
Enhanced capacity of counties to undertake devolved environmental functions (#3 pilot tested)
Number of counties that have pilot tested the process for strengthening CIDPs through alignment with county EPIs, SOEs, EAPs and SEAs.
Reduced Environmental Crime
Environmental Performance Index (EPI) and/or Environmetal Crime Index (ECI) identified as the measure of assessing reduction / growth of environmental crimes in Kenya
Reduced environmental crime (#3 control audits of high risk facilities)
Total number of control audits of high risk facilities annually during this DE.

Environmental functions mainstreamed in ministries, departments and agencies (MDAs) and their implementation reported back to the Performance Contracting Secretariat (#1 environmental policies and action plans)
No. of MDAs with operational environmental policies and action plans (EPAPs) (milestone indicator)
DISCONTINUED: Environmental functions mainstreamed in ministries, departments and agencies (MDAs) and their implementation reported back to the Performance Contracting Secretariat

No. of MDAs with and implementing their environmental policies and action plans. (The indicator was not used since it is not a good measure of MDA performance. Reporting environmental crime cases depends on the amount of environmental crime as well as the responsiveness etc of the MDA that encounters the crime. )
